[src:complete-game/1944-major-league-baseball-season] However, it would not be until after Landis' death in November 1944 that baseball would begin to move towards breaking the color line.
[src:complete-game/1944-major-league-baseball-season] The 1944 schedule consisted of 154 games for all teams in the American League and National League, each of which had eight teams.
[src:complete-game/1944-major-league-baseball-season] Opening Day took place on April 18, featuring fourteen teams.
