[src:complete-game/1944-major-league-baseball-season] Over 78 home games, the Cleveland Indians played 43 games at Cleveland Stadium and 35 games at League Park.
[src:complete-game/1944-major-league-baseball-season] All Sunday home games took place at Cleveland Stadium.
[src:complete-game/1944-major-league-baseball-season] All Saturday home games took place at League Park.
[src:complete-game/1944-major-league-baseball-season] This would be the 10th of 12 seasons since 1932 that saw the Indians play at both venues.
