[src:complete-game/1954-major-league-baseball-season] The **1954 major league baseball season** began on April 13, 1954.
[src:complete-game/1954-major-league-baseball-season] The regular season ended on September 26, with the New York Giants and Cleveland Indians as the regular season champions of the National League and American League, respectively.
[src:complete-game/1954-major-league-baseball-season] The postseason began with Game 1 of the 51st World Series on September 29 and ended with Game 4 on October 2.
[src:complete-game/1954-major-league-baseball-season] The Giants swept the Indians in four games, capturing their fifth championship in franchise history, since their previous in 1933.
