[src:complete-game/1954-major-league-baseball-season] During the 1953 Winter Meetings, the National League relaxed requirements for relocation, changing the necessary votes from unanimous between the eight teams to 75% (effectively six).
[src:complete-game/1954-major-league-baseball-season] This eased the eventual relocation of the Giants and Dodgers to California in 1958.
