[src:complete-game/1964-major-league-baseball-season] Louis Cardinals defeating the New York Yankees in the 1964 World Series in seven games.
[src:complete-game/1964-major-league-baseball-season] The New York Mets leave the Polo Grounds (where they played for two seasons) and open Shea Stadium (with the AFL's New York Jets) where they would go on to play 45 seasons through 2008.
